The Vice Chancellor (VC) of the University of Jos (Unijos), Prof Ishaya Tanko, has urged students of the university to report any attempt of sexual harassment by either lecturers, students or other individuals outside the university campus to the schoolâ€™s management. Prof Tanko, who said this while fielding questions from journalists at the university, said the university had a clear door policy for students and staff to report any sexual harassment. He said though they had not received any case yet, the university would not relent in ensuring that female students and staff were protected.